  "texts": [
    "We conclude that G ′ also acts by isometries of g B.",
    "Since G consists of automorphisms of N, we can form the semi-direct product G ′ ⋉ N. This acts naturally on M ≃ B × N by(φ, n) • (b, x) = (φ • b, φ(n • x)).Clearly this action is transitive.",
    "It is also isometric sinceφ * (g B + h φ(b)) = g B + (φ -1 • h φ(b)) = g B + h b.Hence, the claim holds in this case.Suppose now that h is any ρ-equivariant totally geodesic map.",
    "By [Vil70, Thm.",
    "2.2], we can factor h intoh = h ′ • η,where η: B → B′ is a totally geodesic Riemannian submersion and h ′: B′ → G/K is a totally geodesic immersion."
